-- S.Korean shares fall 1 pct on nagging growth worries; won lower  
-- By Joonhee Yu
-- Fri Oct 17, 2014 02:20AM EDT
-- None



SEOUL, Oct 17 (Reuters) - South Korean shares fell nearly 1 percent on Friday as investors cut their risk exposure amid mounting fears of slowing global growth and a possible renewal in the euro zone's debt crisis.

The Korea Composite Stock Price Index (KOSPI) <.KS11> fell 0.95 percent to close at 1,900.66 points, dipping below 1,900 points in late trade for the first time since Feb. 6. The index loss 2.1 percent on the week. The South Korean won <KRW=> softened, weighed as offshore investors repatriated their funds to record an 11th straight net selling session.